li.p:
 Standard form: y=ax^2+bx+c 


vertical intercept: c

zeros:  \displaystyle \frac{-b\pm \sqrt{b^2-4ac}}{2a}

setup.pg-code:
Context("Fraction");

$a = Compute(random(2,6,1));
do {$k = Compute(random(2,6,1))} until (gcd($a,$k)==1);
$r = Compute(random(2,6,1));
$c = $k*-$r;
$b = $a*-$r+$k;
$quadratic = Formula("$a x^2 + $b x + $c")->reduce;
$x1 = Fraction($r,1);
$x2 = Fraction(-$k,$a);
Context()->flags->set(reduceConstants=>0,reduceConstantFunctions=>0);
$solnum1 = Formula("-$b+sqrt(($b)**2-4($a)($c))");
$solnum2 = Formula("-$b-sqrt(($b)**2-4($a)($c))");

$evaluatorfora = $a->cmp()->withPostFilter(AnswerHints(
    [-$a] =>
    "Do you have the sign correct?"));
$evaluatorforb = $b->cmp()->withPostFilter(AnswerHints(
    [-$b] =>
    "Do you have the sign correct?"));
$evaluatorforc = $c->cmp()->withPostFilter(AnswerHints(
    [-$c] =>
    "Do you have the sign correct?"));

$a=Compute(random(2,9,1));
$coeff=Compute(list_random(0.1,0.2,0.4,0.5,0.8));
$const=-$a*$coeff*20;
$constAbs=-$const;
$r=4/$coeff;
$evaluatorforConst = $const->cmp()->withPostFilter(AnswerHints([-$const] => "Is 3-x equal to x-3?"));
$multians = MultiAnswer($r,0.2)->with(
singleResult => 0,
checker => sub {
my ($correct,$student,$self) = @_;
my ($s1, $s2) = @{$student};
my ($c1, $c2) = @{$correct};
return (1,1) if ($c1 == $s1 and $c2 == $s2) or
                ($c1 == $s2 and $c2 == $s1);
return (1,0) if $c1 == $s1 or $c2 == $s1;
return (0,1) if $c1 == $s2 or $c2 == $s2;
return (0,0);
}
);

$a=Compute(random(2,9,1));
$b=Compute(random(2,9,1));
$c=$b+1;

$a=Compute(random(2,9,1));
$aSq=$a**2;
$aTwo=2*$a;

$a=Compute(random(75,99,1));
$c=Compute(random(15,50,1));
$const=-(55**2-4*$a*$c);

solution.p:
To find the zeros, we solve the equation 0=  x^2+55x+ .  This does not appear to be factorable.  Thus, we use the quadratic formula with a= , b=55, and c= :

                            x \amp =\amp  \frac{-55\pm\sqrt{55^2-4(  )( )}}{2(  )}
                            x \amp =\amp  \frac{-55\pm\sqrt{- }}{178}

setup.pg-code:
$m=Compute(random(2,4,1));
$negativeZero=Compute(random(-7,-3,1));
$negativeZeroAbs=-$negativeZero;
do {$positiveZero=Compute(random(2,8,1)); } until ($positiveZero+$negativeZero > 0);
$a=$m;
$aTwo=2*$a;
$bAbs=$m*($positiveZero+$negativeZero);
$bSq=$bAbs**2;
$cAbs=-$m*$negativeZero*$positiveZero;
$const=4*($a)*($cAbs);
$rootSq=$bSq+$const;
$root=sqrt($rootSq);
$ListAns=List("$negativeZero,$positiveZero");

solution.p:
We solve for r in the equation Q(r)= r^2- r-=0 using the quadratic formula with a=, b=- and c=-.

                            r\amp =\amp \frac{-(-) \pm \sqrt{(-)^2-4()(-)}}{2()}
                            r\amp =\amp \frac{ \pm \sqrt{+}}{}
                            r\amp =\amp \frac{ \pm \sqrt{}}{}
                            r\amp =\amp \frac{ \pm }{}

